r","50 - 100 g single cream, to taste"]}],"id":"r365448","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-D4vXQLl0fTE\/XZaphdyUY_I\/AAAAAAAAhRo\/g0OIlz6lhxgZSzSuC5z8QExIajao63RLgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_166qNhkcXy22Uu_D.png","title":"Pea and Ginger Soup, Lemon Salmon with Broccoli and Potatoes","publishedAt":"2019-03-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"44 g","fat":"44 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"30 g","calories":"2984 kJ \/ 713 kcal"},"usefulItems":"tea towel, baking paper, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["A quick, healthy meal full of bright flavours and colours, starting with a vibrant green pea soup with zingy ginger, followed by lemon-marinated salmon with steamed potatoes and broccoli. This multi-level recipe can turn a weeknight dinner into a special treat.","If making a carrot soup instead of a pea soup, make sure carrots are cut in small pieces.","If the celery stalks have leaves, place a few leaves on top of salmon fillets before steaming to add extra flavour.","For a milder taste, omit drizzling salmon with marinade in <nobr>step 4.<\/nobr>","After serving the soup, set mixing bowl and covered Varoma back in position so the main course keeps warm while the soup is enjoyed."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","45m","4 portions"]}